<h2 class="bold font-l">Harry Potter</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
Alastor 'Mad-Eye' Moody demonstrates to the students the three Unforgivable Curses: Imperio (the Imperius Curse), Crucio (the Cruciatus Curse), and Avada Kedavra (the Killing Curse). These three spells are known as such for being the most powerful and sinister spells known to the wizarding world, and their usage on another human being would often warrant a life sentence to Azkaban. </p>
<p class='example_row'>Example of:<br><a href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DangerousForbiddenTechnique" class='trope-example-link'>Dangerous Forbidden Technique</a></p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="51xtd0" data-video-descrip="First instance of Priori Incantatem in the Harry Potter franchise, as seen in Goblet of Fire" data-video-title="Priori Incantatem" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/51xtd0_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/51xtd0.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/BeamOWar" data-video-tropename="Beam-O-War" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="Film/HarryPotterAndTheGobletOfFire,Film/HarryPotter" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/51xtd0.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">Priori Incantatem</span></p>
